text: The Scion FR-s is a sports car developed by Toyota and Subaru. It features a rear wheel drive drivetrain and 2+2 seating. It is sold worldwide under three different brands with respective model names: * Toyota 86 in Asia, South Africa, North America (from August 2016), South America and Australia; GT86 in Europe; New Zealand; FT86 in Nicaragua and Jamaica; * Subaru BRZ worldwide; * Scion FR-S in the US and Canada. After August 2016, the Scion FR-S will be renamed as the Toyota 86. == References == Category:Sports cars Category:Subaru
